article.description: Chasity Melvin scored 17 points, including the go-ahead basket with 4 seconds left, as the host Cleveland Rockers rallied past the Indiana Fever 71-67 Sunday night.
article.headline: Melvin scores 15 points in second half
article.linkText: Rockers turn up heat on Fever
article.story:
CLEVELAND (AP) -- Chasity Melvin got a courtside wake-up call and
went to work.

Melvin scored 17 points, including the go-ahead basket with 4
seconds left, as the Cleveland Rockers rallied past the Indiana
Fever 71-67 Sunday night.

"I started to think how tired I was," Melvin said. "A fan
yelled, 'Come on, Chas, wake up!' I said to myself, 'You're right,
suck it up and make it happen.' I was determined."

Cleveland (14-14) took a one-game lead over the Fever (13-15) in
the race for the final playoff berth in the Eastern Conference by
sweeping a home-and-home weekend series.

"We'll enjoy this one, but have to get ready for Connecticut,"
Rockers coach Dan Hughes said. "Every game is just so
meaningful."

Cleveland moved into a third-place tie with Connecticut and will
host the Sun on Thursday night.

Tamika Catchings led Indiana with 21 points, 10 assists and
seven steals, but the Fever lost their fifth in a row and sixth in
seven games.

"Catchings is remarkable," Hughes said. "She made some
marvelous plays, but I'm happy with the way we responded,
especially Chas. She really wanted the ball and played strong
inside."

With the score tied at 67, Melvin drove across the lane and hit
a 6-footer to put Cleveland ahead. Merlakia Jones hit two free
throws with 2.7 seconds left for the final margin.

Melvin scored 15 points in the second half, including six
straight in a 10-0 run that put Cleveland ahead 60-59 with 6:18
left. She pumped her arms wildly to rally her teammates after the
sixth point.

Penny Taylor and Deanna Jackson hit 3-pointers to end the
run.

A layup by Natalie Williams put Indiana back in front, and again
Cleveland played catch-up for three minutes -- until a layup by
Melvin gave the Rockers a 65-64 lead with 2:20 left.

LaToya Thomas, who also scored 17 points for Cleveland, made one
free throw with 1:34 left. Melvin hit another with 51.5 seconds
remaining to make it 67-64.

Catchings scored on a layup seven seconds later and Niele Ivey
made one of two free throws with 26.8 seconds left to tie it at 67.

"At key points, we just did not knock down the shot," the
Fever's Kelly Schumacher said. "The wrong things happened at the
wrong time for us."

Williams and Schumacher scored 12 points apiece for Indiana.

The win gave Cleveland a 3-0 record against Indiana and the edge
in the tiebreaker with the Fever. The teams will meet for the last
time in the regular season Aug. 23 in Indiana.
